title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 94 AE with Scope
location: San Antonio Area, Texas, United States
postcontent:
I am selling one of my model 94AE, this gun has a new scope (9x40) and sling, last week of the season I took a nice doe at 187 yards with this gun so I know she is dead on.

The gun is 90% clean, lots of steel and wood. It's just made the old fashioned way. Lots of durable steel parts that feel solid and reliable.

Incredible design. John Moses Browning really outdid himself when he designed the Model 94. The mechanism is smooth and precise. The ergonomics are practically perfect. The action is strong and simply not prone to wearing out.

Solid lockup. The John Browning design was created to handle the newest type of ammunition in the world at the time: smokeless powder loads. And it is still handling them. The Model 94 has been chambered in some of the meanest calibers ever developed for fast action in brushy conditions.

It's a lifetime gun. Some rifles come and go, but a Model 94 just builds a lifetime of memories. It is one gun that your family will appreciate long after you are gone. It's a gun your great grandson will learn to shoot with. Timeless. That is why I have two of them!

Today's great barrels mean the 94 is more accurate than ever. And there are more bullet choices too. And factory ammo is a lot more affordable than some other calibers, making it something you can afford to shoot.

110 years ago my ancestors bought 94s because they were cool, fast handling and had high magazine capacity. 


If you are interested in the gun text me at REDACTED, or email me at REDACTED

title: Want To Buy:  Your votes and dollars!
postcontent:
I am employed by an agency that does canvassing for campaigns all over the west coast, most of which are left wing. Our most recent assignment is door-to-door petition work in Reno and Sparks in order to get an effect on the 2016 ballot that, if passed, would require background checks for unlicensed gun sales. My agency has brought in ~200 people on buses from Seattle, Portland, and Tacoma to try to push this through before the deadline on Wednesday.
Although I am unfamiliar with the Reno area, I came here expecting a high amount of opposition in the form of slammed doors and rude refusals. Nevada is a red state and even in uber-liberal Washington this is really just part of the job. What I found strange was the fact that they couldn't just pay people in Reno to do this work. Why was our agency paying to bring people in from Washington and Oregon, 15-12 hours away?
Last night, during a 3-9pm shift, some things happened to my co-workers that have made me think that we were brought in because locals KNOW BETTER than to do liberal canvassing here. One woman was assaulted and mugged right after the sun went down in Sparks. This was only a couple of blocks from where my friend and roommate was working. The cops picked my friend up and told him to leave because they believed a group of people were riding around in a truck looking for canvassers to beat up. At least five of my co-workers were verbally assaulted or followed at night. One woman had a shotgun pulled on her at a door and was then followed by the gun-owner, who had the gun with him in his car. A black co-worker had a pistol pulled on him and put to his head at a door. I have been kicked out of neighborhoods by homeowners, mostly gated communities, screamed at, told to fuck off, and have been greeted by men behind doors holding knives defensively. I understand that no one likes to hear their doorbell ring in the middle of dinner, but we are only doing our jobs. We are not soliciting as we are not selling anything. Everything we are doing is perfectly legal within our constitutional right to free speech.
I opted out of the pm shift tonight because I legitimately fear for my safety and many others have done the same. Most of our problems came up when we started working in Sparks and, although the agency has claimed they are not sending people there anymore, I know of four people who had turf in that area this morning. Locals - what neighborhoods are considered unsafe here in Reno and Sparks? Where would you not want to find yourself alone with a gun control petition after dark? We need your help to protect ourselves while we continue to just do our jobs here. I would hate to see another person threatened or assaulted before I leave.

http://www.reddit.com/r/Reno/comments/2ltbos/im_working_on_a_gun_control_petition_going/

We need to outlaw this in Nevada, no outside people working around our elections!

In the Czech Republic (where it was born), it is the most common CCW pistol (the Czech Republic is a 'shall issue' country, rare for Europe), from the fine gun craftsmen at CZ, who despite being little-known in the US, have been *the* go to pistol makers for most of Europe and the rest of the world. The Distributor is CZ USA, in Kansas. Fear not, it is stamped "MADE IN CZECH REPUBLIC" on the opposite side.

 This model in particular is the "alloy" model, made of lighter (but equally strong) metal than its heavier predecessor and (discontinued) polymer cousins.

 The Pistol is an "A" series, one of the 1st 1000 made. It was made in 2003 during the dark era known as the Assault Weapons Ban, therefore coming with two 10 round magazines, which can be supplemented with floorplates or just by sticking CZ75 magazines in it. It has glow sights which sit quite high for a very clear sight picture.

  The pistol is interesting in the way the action is a DA/SA, but has a SAO style (CZ or 1911) safety system. It can be carried hammer down, safety off (the DA trigger is stout enough to act as a safety in itself, like a revolver), half cocked or fully cocked with safety on. The controls are generously-sized and ergonomically-superb.

  Accuracy? I love the accuracy of this pistol. It is amazingly smooth to shoot with little to no felt recoil. I would go so far as to recommend this SubCompact to the arthritic, elderly, novice or female (no sexism, just going from patterns of things countless female shooters have told me they prefer in a semi-auto). The reliability is superb, with zero-failures in its loyal service rendered unto me. This is the Mercedes Benz of subcompacts- reliable, dutiful and still resplendent with class and head-turning distinction. 

Prices for these guns range from 575-600+, according to research done to compare prices. However, I am a believer that a used gun is a used gun. Too many unsavory individuals are selling used guns at MSRP and I shall not partake of such thievery. My price is fair appeasement value, quite literally "by the book"

You will receive two (2) magazines. The pistol is superb and I am more than willing to even sweeten the deal by offering the original box, a TSA-approved hardened steel safe-type case with key or a nice CZ case of a later model CZ pistol I own (simulated leather texture, black with gold closure snaps).

I do not want your Hi-points, your Lorcins, Rugers, or anything of the like. My "trade" list is below. I will most likely not deviate from that. 

I am Mister Wolf, I can be reached (by text) at REDACTED.
